+# Codex Writer Findings — StaffOrdersMobile
+Chain: staffordersmobile-260415-225055-2937
+
+## Findings
+1. [P1] Fix B is not applied in `closeSession` — `components/sessionHelpers.js:175-177` still fetches requests with `base44.entities.ServiceRequest.filter({ table: tableId })`. That keeps the close-table path dependent on `table` link normalization, so requests tied to the session but mismatched on `table` can stay open and continue triggering `hasActiveRequest` in the Active tab. FIX: replace the primary query with `ServiceRequest.filter({ table_session: sessionId })`, then fall back to `table: tableId` only when the session query returns zero rows; keep the existing sequential update loop and `BATCH_DELAY_MS` unchanged.
+2. [P1] Fix C.1 is not applied in `activeOrders` — `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/260415-00 StaffOrdersMobile RELEASE.jsx:3580-3583` still returns `o.status !== 'cancelled'` for finish-stage orders. That lets `status='closed'` orders from an old session remain in `activeOrders`, repopulate `orderGroups`, and surface on a reopened table as if they were still relevant to the active workflow. FIX: change the finish-stage passthrough to exclude both `closed` and `cancelled` orders.
+3. [P0] Fix C.2 is not applied in `handleCloseTableClick` — `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/260415-00 StaffOrdersMobile RELEASE.jsx:2164-2171` still derives `sessionId` with `group.orders.map(...).find(Boolean)`. On a mixed table containing historical closed orders plus a new open session, that code can pick the old session first and close the wrong session while leaving the real open session active. FIX: prefer `group.openSessionId` from the open-session source of truth, and only fall back to the first non-closed/non-cancelled order that still has `table_session`.
+4. [P1] Fix A ground truth is missing — the RELEASE file has no `openSessions` query or `openSessionByTableId` map near the query block (`3513-3526`), no `openSessionId` field in the table-group builder (`3740-3789`), and no TableSession override in `filteredGroups` / `tabCounts` (`3832-3871`). The page still decides Active vs Completed only from orders and requests, so one stale signal can keep a closed table in Active, and a table with no visible orders/requests can disappear instead of being forced into Completed. FIX: add a `useQuery` for open `TableSession` rows, derive `openSessionByTableId`, attach `openSessionId` to table groups, and short-circuit table groups in `filteredGroups` and `tabCounts` to Completed when no open session exists.
+5. [P1] Fix A cache refresh is missing in `confirmCloseTable` — `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/260415-00 StaffOrdersMobile RELEASE.jsx:4146-4155` refreshes orders and service requests only. Once the TableSession ground truth is added, this handler will still leave the tab classification stale until a later refresh unless it explicitly invalidates the new `openSessions` query. FIX: add `queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["openSessions"] })` immediately after `closeSession(sessionId, tableId)` alongside the existing refresh path.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 5 findings (1 P0, 4 P1, 0 P2, 0 P3)
+
